cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of NeuroEvolution, which is a subfield of machine learning that combines neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the improvement of solutions to complex problems, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of the method to a robot duel domain suggests that it could also fall under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
